{
  "texts": [
    "This all-optical data-class-specific transformation system was experimentally demonstrated in different parts of the electromagnetic spectrum, i.e., 1550 nm and 0.75 mm wavelengths, and can enable fast, energyefficient data encryption using a broad range of optical sources.",
    "As another demonstration in the visible spectrum, a single-layer Si metasurface that could represent a linear complex-valued S-matrix was reported for solving the Fredholm integral equations 85.",
    "This metagrating structure can approximate a Neumann series based on successive reflection between the metasurface and a semitransparent mirror.",
    "This analog computing platform that operates in the visible spectrum enables a highly compact and thin device that can achieve high processing speeds, with the possibility of on-chip integration.",
    "Diffractive networks that process spatially encoded information of light present some unique opportunities for computational imaging and display systems."
  ]
}